      {
        "heading": "Clinical Note",
        "section_value": "He currently takes Coreg for his hypertension and Lexapro for his anxiety. He reports a history of prediabetes, which he has brought under control via dietary changes. He denies any history of thyroid issues.\nREVIEW OF SYSTEMS\n• Constitutional Symptoms: Easily fatigued, weight gain.\n• Eyes: Floaters.\n• Cardiovascular: Bilateral peripheral edema.\n• Respiratory: Shortness of breath.\n• Gastrointestinal: Excessive appetite, abdominal bloating.\n• Musculoskeletal: Gout, muscle pain.\n• Integumentary: Dry itchy skin, nail bed changes.\n• Endocrine: Excessive hunger.",
        "medical_concepts": [
